						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the north wall of a well in the centre of the village.</p>						

						<p>[Tribhu]vanamalladēva.</p>						

						<p>This record, the later portion of which is built in, refers itself to the reign <hi rend="bold">• • namalladēva</hi> who was ruling from his capital <hi rend="bold">Kalyāṇa.</hi> The king might be Vikramāditya VI. But no other details are forthcoming.</p>						

						</summary>
